<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="1" id="97973dad-b139-5170-9aa7-bd45a0dea6ac" activityNameId="c1fd48aa-2a62-478c-8f4e-d34dff0bee29" parentActivityId="702a9e19-624f-416b-9ff5-17b5a071f2e4" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">market for m-nitrotoluene</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'm-nitrotoluene',  within the geography of Global.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the supply of 'm-nitrotoluene',  to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">This is the market for  'm-nitrotoluene', in the Global geography.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">'m-nitrotoluene' is an organic substance with a CAS no. : 99-08-1. It is called '1-methyl-3-nitrobenzene' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C7H7NO2. It is a clear yellow liquid that freezes at 16.1°C with a weak aromatic odor. The substance is modelled as a pure substance. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on a consumer level. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: chemicals.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
      </geography>
      <technology/>
      <timePeriod startDate="2003-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
